Uktar 29: I ventured out of my quarters to greet a traveller, Miala by name,
	who came to the cathedral today. He is a mystic, and I suspect he is
	a remnant of the old druidic order that broke up many years ago. He
	seemed to look through me, and he said to me, "Your night lies close
	at hand, but this stone will save you from the darkness." He gave to
	me a large gem, about the size of my fist, that was pale blue and
	seemed to pulse with life. I looked into it, but I couldn't sense
	any magic to it. I fear that Miala may be as mad as I soon may be.

